race.comment: FOREMAN'S GULLY (1) turned things around last start when he demolished his rivals with the 62kg over 1175m at this track. No reason he can't do it again with the claim. NEESON (6) progressive gelding who jumped sharply in grade third-up when a handy third over 1300m at Canberra in a TAB Federal. Placed to advantage from the low barrier. LITTLE BASHEBA (8) finished second at Corowa two runs back, then was less effective when slow into stride for a battling seventh over 1180m at Gundagai. Improver on her home track. COMPLAISANCE (15) stepped up in trip to 1400m when a tiring eighth at Gundagai in a solid rating contest. Back to her preferred trip and stays in the mix. SANTOLINI (10) caught the eye last start and goes into the exotics.
